commentPostTextItems.html: Teams coming back to the ground for the presentation
Man of the match awarded to Peter Borren.  Great going for him, another one after he bagged the same award day before yesterday.
Good bye everyone.  Hope you enjoyed this coverage from Cricinfo. This is Sandeep Harnal signing off.  See you tomorrow morning for the final and last ODI between these two teams.

dismissalComment.html: That's all over for Canada little short of a length, returned an easy one back to the bowler

milestones.description: Atse Buurman and Peter Borren's 118-run partnership is NED's highest for the 6th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 78 between Ryan ten Doeschate and Kervezee
Dhaniram and Steven Welsh's 54-run partnership is CAN's highest for the 9th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 31 between Kevin Sandher and Codrington
Steven Welsh and Henry Osinde's 44-run partnership is CAN's highest for the 10th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 36 between Codrington and Henry Osinde
Netherlands's 118-run win against Canada is the largest margin of victory in terms of runs in ODIs, beating 64-run win against Namibia

stories.title: Canada battered to emphatic defeat
stories.subTitle: Canada v Netherlands, 1st ODI, Toronto
stories.summary: Netherlands romped to 117-run victory over Canada in the first of two ODIs at the Toronto Cricket, Skating and Curling Club, but the manner of their victory was far more emphatic than the final margin suggests
